Customize Your Work Summaries in Copilot (Generally Available)

You can now customize how Einstein drafts Work Summaries in Copilot. Get summaries that meet your team's needs by adding your own formatting rules or restrictions to the prompt template that guides Einstein responses.

This change applies to Lightning Experience, the Salesforce mobile app for iOS and Android, the Field Service mobile app for iOS and Android, and Sales Cloud Everywhere in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited editions with the Einstein for Sales, Einstein for Service, or Einstein Platform add-on.

To use this feature, users must have the Use Einstein Copilot for Salesforce user permission. To customize prompt templates, users must also have the Execute Prompt Templates user permission.

The Summarize Record standard copilot action uses a Summarize Messaging Session or Summarize Voice Call prompt template to generate summaries. You can create or customize these templates by following the instructions in Ingredients of a Prompt Template.

SEE ALSO

* Show AI-Generated Summaries with Einstein Work Summaries
* Prompt Builder
* Einstein Copilot
title: Customizing Einstein Work Summaries
